# Auto Loader — schema evolution modes

Auto Loader caches the schema at `schemaLocation`; `schemaEvolutionMode` decides what a new column does.

| Mode | On a new column |
|---|---|
| **`addNewColumns`** (default) | Stream fails; restart evolves + continues |
| **`rescue`** | Continues; unknowns → `_rescued_data` |
| **`failOnNewColumns`** | Fails until you evolve it yourself |
| **`none`** | Silently ignored |

- **`_rescued_data`** captures anything that didn't fit (new column, uncastable value) as JSON — with `rescue`, **nothing is silently dropped**
- **`schemaHints`** pin types without a full schema

**Exam:** `addNewColumns` = production default; `rescue` = never lose data.
